adjectives.description: unattaining (comparative more unattaining, superlative most unattaining)

entries.meaning: That does not lead to attainment
examples: There she clutches at illusions, and she seeks the phantom goal
With the unattaining passion that consumes the unsleeping soul:
And calamity enfolds her, like the shadow of a ban,
And the niggardness of Nature makes the misery of man;
